<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-549-735  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 549 735.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Oct 22 1990 n391 p107(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hearst to install PC-based StarMIS editorial-management system:publishing giant enters electronic-publishing world.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Calderbank, Alison.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Hearst Corp has contracted with National Electrographics CompanyInc to install a computer-based management system to trackeditorial and art work at nine of its magazines.andP;  The system iscalled StarMIS for Story Tracking Art Retrieval ManagementInformation System.andP;  The system is designed to help integrate thestory writing and word processing aspects of the magazines thatare often done on IBM-compatible machines, with the art and layoutwork that is done on Apple Macintoshes.andP;  The system is based onOdesta Corp's Document Management Systems; a system NationalElectrographics sells as a value added reseller.andP;  Hearst hopes thesystem will cut production time and save money.andP;  Hearst installedthe system as a trial at one magazine and saved 23.7 percent ofits production costs.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hearst Corp. (Automation)National Electragraphics Company Inc. (Services).andO;Product:   ODMS (Search software) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Document Management SystemsMagazinesPublishing IndustryConnectivityMISMultivendor Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>